- 2.0.1 | Feb 26 2026:
  [New] tlog_lib.sh: shared Bash library for incremental log file reading
      with cursor-based position tracking; multi-mode tracking (byte-offset
      via tail -c, line-count via tail -n) selectable per call or TLOG_MODE
      env; mode-aware cursor format (bare number = bytes, L:N = lines) with
      automatic mismatch detection and reset; configurable first-run behavior
      (TLOG_FIRST_RUN=skip|full); structured error codes 0-4; source guard
      prevents double-sourcing
  [New] Atomic cursor writes via mktemp + mv -f; optional flock-based
      cursor locking (TLOG_FLOCK=1) with 5-second timeout; cursor validation
      with regex check and auto-reset on corruption; stale cursor protection
      via mtime touch on every tlog_read call
  [New] Rotation-aware delta reads: .1 and .1.gz discovery with bounds
      checking; .gz read via zcat pipe (read-only, never decompresses on disk)
  [New] tlog_adjust_cursor(): mode-aware cursor subtraction for in-place
      log trim with clamp-to-zero; tlog_advance_cursors(): fast-forward
      multiple file and journal cursors from FILE|TAG pairs
  [New] Journal support: registry-based filter system via parallel indexed
      arrays (avoids declare -A scope issues); tlog_journal_register() for
      consuming projects to define service-to-journalctl mappings;
      tlog_journal_read() cursor-based with timestamp fallback;
      tlog_journal_read_full() for scan mode with timeout support
  [New] Standalone tlog CLI wrapper: sources tlog_lib.sh with security
      check (root ownership, not world-writable); backward-compatible
      argument parsing (file, tlog_name, optional mode); BASERUN
      sed-replaced at install time for cursor storage security
  [New] BATS test suite: 74 tests covering both tracking modes, rotation,
      cursor validation, flock locking, atomic writes, journal, and
      standalone CLI; Docker infrastructure for Debian 12, Rocky 9,
      CentOS 6 with parallel execution
  [New] README.md: public-facing documentation with platform support matrix,
      API reference, security guidance for cursor storage, and usage examples
  [Change] Migrate test infrastructure to batsman shared framework via git
      submodule at tests/infra/; thin project-layer Dockerfiles for 9 OS
      targets (debian12, centos6, centos7, rocky8, rocky9, rocky10,
      ubuntu1204, ubuntu2004, ubuntu2404); batsman-driven orchestration
      replaces custom run-tests.sh and Makefile; GitHub Actions CI via
      batsman reusable workflow
  [New] _tlog_is_compressed() and _tlog_cat_file(): generic decompression
      dispatch supporting gzip, xz, bzip2, zstd, lz4 via -dc flags
  [Change] _tlog_find_rotated() extended with .1.xz, .1.bz2, .1.zst, .1.lz4
      compressed rotated file discovery; runtime tool availability check via
      command -v; uncompressed .1 retains highest priority
  [Change] tlog_read() rotation refactored from hardcoded gzip/zcat to generic
      compression dispatch via _tlog_is_compressed/_tlog_cat_file
  [New] Copytruncate and multi-format compression rotation tests with
      false-positive coverage; test Dockerfiles add xz, bzip2, zstd packages
  [New] Standalone tlog CLI expansion: option parsing (-m/--mode, -b/--baserun,
      -f/--flock, --first-run), subcommands (--full, --status, --reset,
      --adjust), version banner (-v/--version), short help (-h), detailed
      help with examples (--help); full backward compatibility with positional
      interface preserved
  [New] --status subcommand: display cursor state (path, mode, value, age),
      optional file argument shows size and pending delta, reports .jts and
      .lock presence; read-only â€” does not modify any files
  [New] --reset subcommand: delete cursor, .jts, .lock, and orphaned temp
      files; reports each deletion; always exits 0
  [New] --adjust subcommand: delegates to tlog_adjust_cursor() for mode-aware
      cursor subtraction after in-place log trimming
  [New] --full subcommand: delegates to tlog_read_full() for cursorless
      full-file reads; does not require BASERUN
  [New] Standalone CLI test expansion: 46 new tests (56 total) covering
      help/version, option flags, all subcommands, error handling,
      false-positive verification, and path traversal rejection
  [Fix] Cursor name path traversal: reject names containing '/' or equal
      to '.'/'..'; prevents --reset, --status, --adjust, and read from
      operating on files outside the BASERUN directory
  [Fix] Tracking mode validation in tlog CLI wrapper: reject invalid mode
      values (e.g., 'line' instead of 'lines') in both -m flag and positional
      argument; prevents silent cursor mismatch reset loop on typos
  [Fix] Tracking mode validation in tlog_lib.sh: tlog_read() rejects invalid
      mode strings before any I/O, returning exit 1 with descriptive error;
      defense-in-depth for programmatic callers (BFD, LMD) beyond CLI
  [Fix] Shellcheck CI: replace incorrect source= directive with
      disable=SC1090,SC1091 for dynamic library source path; resolves lint job
      exit 1 on all CI runs
  [Fix] CentOS 7 journal test: use nonexistent PATH instead of /usr/bin:/bin
      to reliably hide journalctl on systemd systems; avoids POSIX empty-PATH
      CWD-search edge case
